snippet5-2: A tooth abscess is a buildup of pus that can be found inside the teeth, in the gums, or in the mandible. This happens when a bacterial infection takes place in the mouth. Abscesses at the end of a tooth is called a periapical abscess. Tooth or dental abscesses are often painful, but in cases are not.
snippet5-3: When a tooth or the gums surrounding the tooth become infected, an abscess may develop. An abscess is a serious problem and requires immediate attention. A dentist can prescribe antibiotics to reduce the swelling caused by the abscess and make treatment possible, which will also minimize the pain. If the abscess is the result of a cavity in the tooth, it has already been there for an extended period of time. That type of abscess grows slowly and spreads until it ultimately invades the center of the tooth. It attacks the dental pulp in the center of the tooth, which contains nerves and blood vessels.
